{"parse":{"title":"number","pageid":1580,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|nummer||dialectal}}\n* {{alt|en|numbre||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|en|id=quantity|:inh|enm:nombre<id:number>|tree=1}}\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*nem-}}\n{{inh+|en|enm|number}}, {{m|enm|nombre}}, {{m|enm|numbre}}, {{m|enm|noumbre}}, from {{der|en|xno|noumbre|sc=Latn}}, {{der|en|fro|nombre|sc=Latn}}, from {{der|en|la|numerus||number}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*nem-||to divide}}. Compare {{cog|stq|Nummer}}, {{m|stq|Nuumer}}, {{cog|fy|nûmer}}, {{cog|nl|nummer||number}}, {{cog|de|Nummer||number}}, {{cog|da|nummer||number}}, {{cog|sv|nummer||number}}, {{cog|is|númer||number}}. Replaced Middle English {{m|enm|ȝetæl}} and {{m|enm|rime}}, more at {{m|en|tell}}, {{m|en|tale}} and {{m|en|rhyme}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{enPR|nŭmʹbər}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈnʌmbər/}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈnʌmbə]|a=RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈnʌ̟mbɚ]|a=US,CA}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-number.ogg|a=US}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈnɐmbɐ]|a=AU}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈnʌmbəɾ]|a=Scotland}}\n* {{enPR|no͝omʹbər|a=Northern England}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈnʊmbə/}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ʌmbə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|num|ber}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|quantity}} [[quantity|Quantity]] of [[countable]] things.\n#: {{ux|en|Any '''number''' of people can be reading from a given repository at a time.}}\n#: {{ux|en|There are, in addition to all the red socks, a '''number''' that don’t suit me either.}} \n#: {{ux|en|The '''number''' of malnourished children has decreased.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-08|volume=407|issue=8839|page=52|magazine=w:The Economist|title=[http://www.economist.com/news/international/21579039-chinas-growing-empire-ports-abroad-mainly-about-trade-not-aggression-new-masters The new masters and commanders]|passage=From the ground, Colombo’s port does not look like much.{{...}}&nbsp; But viewed from high up in one of the growing '''number''' of skyscrapers in Sri Lanka’s capital, it is clear that something extraordinary is happening: China is creating a shipping hub just 200 miles from India’s southern tip.}}\n#* {{RQ:Bacon Essayes|chapter=Of the True Greatness of Kingdoms and Estates|passage='''Number''' itself importeth not much in armies where the people are of weak courage.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} An [[abstract]] [[entity]] used to [[describe]] [[quantity]].\n#: {{ux|en|Zero, one, −1, 2.5, and pi are all '''numbers'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[numeral]]: a [[symbol]] for a [[non-negative]] [[integer]].\n#: {{syn|en|scalar|rime|q2=obsolete}}\n#: {{ux|en|The '''number''' 8 is usually made with a single stroke.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Edward Helmore|title=What does ‘8647’ really mean? Not what Trump’s supporters are saying|magazine=w:The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/may/16/8647-meaning-james-comey-instagram-trump|date=2025-05-16|passage=The former FBI director James Comey has said it did not occur to him that that the '''numbers''' 8647 – which he spotted spelled out in seashells on a beach, and posted on social media – could be interpreted as a call to assassinate the president, as many supporters of Donald Trump have claimed.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable|mathematics}} An [[element]] of one of several [[sets]]: [[natural number]]s, [[integer]]s, [[rational number]]s, [[real number]]s, [[complex number]]s, and sometimes extensions such as [[hypercomplex numbers]], etc.\n#: {{ux|en|The equation <math>e^{i\\pi}+1=0</math> includes the most important '''numbers''': 1, 0, <math>\\pi</math>, <math>i</math>, and <math>e</math>.}}\n# {{lb|en|Followed by a [[numeral]]; used [[attributive]]ly}} Indicating the position of something in a list or sequence. Abbreviations: ''[[No]]'' or ''[[No.]]'', ''[[no]]'' or ''[[no.]]'' (in each case, sometimes written with a superscript \"o\", like Nº or &#x2116;). The symbol \"#\" is also used in this manner.\n#: {{ux|en|Horse '''number''' 5 won the race.}}\n# A [[sequence]] of [[digit]]s and [[letter]]s used to register people, automobiles, and various other items.\n#: {{ux|en|Her passport '''number''' is C01X864TN.}}\n#: {{ux|en|You can take the '''number 8''' (bus) all the way to the airport.}}\n# {{senseid|en|telephone number}} {{lb|en|countable|informal}} A [[telephone number]].\n#: {{ux|en|Let's give her a call. Do you have her '''number''' handy?}}\n#: {{ux|en|I'm definitely interested. Here's my '''number'''. Call me back anytime.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|title=w:Rikki Don't Lose That Number|artist=w:Steely Dan|year=1974|passage=Rikki, don't lose that '''number''' /  You don't wanna call nobody else  / Send it off in a letter to yourself}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2001|author=E. Forrest Hein|title=The Ruach Project,|publisher=Xulon Press|page=86\n|passage=“[...] I wonder if you could get hold of him and have him call me here at Interior. I’m in my office, do you have my '''number'''?”}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2007|author=Lindsey Nicole Isham|title=No Sex in the City: One Virgin's Confessions on Love, Lust, Dating, and Waiting|publisher=Kregel Publications|page=111\n|passage=When I agreed to go surfing with him he said, “Great, can I have your '''number'''?” Well, I don’t give my '''number''' to guys I don’t know.}}\n#* '''2016''', [https://web.archive.org/web/20170918070146/https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/lets-learn-english-lesson-3-i-am-here/3126527.html VOA Learning English] (public domain)\n#*: Marsha's work '''number''' is 555-8986.\n# {{senseid|en|grammar}}{{lb|en|grammar}} Of a word or phrase, the state of being [[singular]], [[dual]] or [[plural]], shown by [[inflection]].\n#: {{ux|en|Adjectives and nouns should agree in gender, '''number''', and case.}}\n# {{lb|en|now|rare|in the plural}} Poetic metres; [[verse]]s, [[rhyme]]s.\n#* {{RQ:Donne Poems|poem=The Triple Foole|page=204|passage=Griefe brought to '''numbers''' cannot be ſo fierce, / For, he tames it, that fetters it in verſe.}}\n#* {{RQ:Pope Arbuthnot|page=7|lines=124–125|passage=As yet a Child, nor yet a Fool to Fame, / I liſp'd in '''Numbers''', for the '''Numbers''' came.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[performance]]; especially, a single [[song]] or song and dance routine within a larger show.\n#: {{ux|en|For his second '''number''', he sang \"The Moon Shines Bright\".}}\n# {{lb|en|no plural|formal}} A [[group]] of [[people]].\n#: {{uxi|en|I include myself in their '''number'''.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2020-08-22|author=w:Robert McCrum|title=For ever and a day: why we turn to Shakespeare at times of crisis|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2020/aug/22/for-ever-and-a-day-why-we-turn-to-shakespeare-at-times-of-crisis|journal=w:The Observer|passage=As an association, we demonstrate near-Olympic sang-froid. As I write, the gods are smiling upon us, but in the past decade – not to mince words – two of our '''number''' have got divorced, one of us checked into rehab, and all of us have had distressful troubles with teenage kids.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable|informal}} A [[person]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1968|author=Janet Burroway|title=The dancer from the dance: a novel,|publisher=Little, Brown|page=40\n|passage=I laughed. \"Don't doubt that. She's a saucy little '''number'''.\"}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1988|author=w:Erica Jong|title=Serenissima,|publisher=Dell|page=214\n|passage=\"Signorina Jessica,\" says the maid, a saucy little '''number''', \"your father has gone to his prayers and demands that you come to the synagogue at once [...]\"}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2005|author=Denise A. Agnew; Kate Hill; Arianna Hart|title=By Honor Bound,|publisher=Ellora's Cave Publishing|page=207\n|passage=He had to focus on the mission, staying alive and getting out, not on the sexy '''number''' rubbing up against him.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable|informal}} An [[outfit]], particularly a [[stylish]] one.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2007|author=Cesca Martin|title=Agony Angel: So You Think You've Got Problems...,|publisher=Troubador Publishing Ltd|page=134\n|passage=The trouble was I was wearing my backless glittering '''number''' from the night before underneath, so unless I could persuade the office it was National Fancy Dress Day I was doomed to sweat profusely in bottle blue.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2007|author=Lorelei James|title=Running with the Devil|publisher=Samhain Publishing, Ltd|page=46\n|passage=\"I doubt the sexy '''number''' you wore earlier tonight fell from the sky.\"}}\n# {{lb|en|slang|chiefly|US}} A [[marijuana]] cigarette, or [[joint]]; also, a quantity of marijuana bought from a [[dealer]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2005|author=K'wan|title=Hoodlum|publisher=St. Martin's Press|isbn=0312333080|pageurl=https://books.google.es/books?id=qQfTHfHYgM8C&lpg=PA185&dq=%22numbers%22&hl=es&pg=PA1#v=onepage&q&f=false|page=1\n|passage=These were the two that Tommy had chosen to collect a debt owed  to his family by a dude named Heath who ran '''numbers''' out of a grocery store on 131st and Lenox.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2009|author=w:Thomas Pynchon|title=Inherent Vice|page=12|publisher=Vintage|year_published=2010\n|passage=Back at his place again, Doc rolled a '''number''', put on a late movie, found an old T-shirt, and sat tearing it up into short strips {{...}}}}\n# {{lb|en|dated}} An [[issue]] of a [[periodical]] [[publication]].\n#: {{ux|en|the latest '''number''' of a magazine}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=1957 July|author=M. D. Greville|title=A Diamond Jubilee of Railway Memories|journal=Railway Magazine|page=458|text=When, in July, 1897, my father brought home the first '''number''' of ''The Railway Magazine'', I little thought that, sixty years later, I should still be reading it, without having missed a single '''number'''.}}  \n# A large amount, in contrast to a smaller amount; numerical preponderance.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=May 10 1980|author=Al King|title=Braves travel to New England with reputation|journal=The Indiana Gazette\n|passage=Despite last week's woes, the Braves still sport '''numbers''' that would make Christie Brinkley blush.}}\n# An activity; assignment; job, as in [[cushy number]].\n\n=====Hyponyms=====\n{{col4|en\n|0800 number\n|11 o'clock number\n|800 number\n|900 number\n|A number\n|a number of\n|Abbe number\n|abbreviated number\n|accession number\n|account number\n|acid number\n|aggregation number\n|aircraft registration number\n|all-figure number\n|angel number\n|any number of\n|apocalyptic number\n|Archimedes number\n|Armstrong number\n|atomic mass number\n|atomic number| Hopf number\n|Atwood number\n|autonumber\n|Avogadro's number\n|azimuthal quantum number\n|back number\n|Bacon number\n|Bagnold number\n|baryon number\n|basic reproduction number\n|basic reproductive number\n|Bates number\n|Bejan number\n|bib number\n|Biot number\n|book number\n|book-number\n|box number\n|call number\n|carbon number\n|cetane number\n|chromosome number\n|contact number\n|control number\n|coordination number\n|copy number\n|critical Reynolds number\n|crooked number\n|crossnumber\n|Cullum number\n|curb number\n|Cutter number\n|devil's number\n|dial number\n|diamond number\n|disc number\n|Dunbar's number\n|edge number\n|electron number\n|element number\n|E number\n|Erdős number\n|Erdos number\n|f-number\n|falling number\n|false number 9\n|fax number\n|fixed-point number\n|flight number\n|floating-point number\n|frame number\n|Fresnel number\n|Froude number\n|furry number\n|GLIDE number\n|God's number\n|Grabovoi number\n|Greek number\n|Hagberg number\n|Hodges number\n|Horowitz number\n|house number\n|illegal number\n|iodine number\n|IP number\n|item number\n|Kenn number\n|Kirschner number\n|Knudsen number\n|Köchel number\n|Laws number\n|lepton number\n|line number\n|L-number\n|lot number\n|Mach number\n|magic number\n|magnetic quantum number\n|mass number\n|matching numbers\n|mesh number\n|Messier number\n|mobile number\n|model number\n|motor octane number\n|national insurance number\n|natural numbers\n|NI number\n|nothing-up-my-sleeve number\n|number 8\n|number eight\n|number nine\n|number one\n|number 10\n|number ten\n|number 2\n|number two\n|number needed to harm\n|numberless\n|nucleon number\n|numeral\n|occupation number\n|octane number\n|opposite number\n|orbital quantum number\n|oxidation number\n|part number\n|personal identification number\n|phone number\n|PIN number\n|pitting resistance equivalent number\n|Polenske number\n|Prandtl number\n|preferred number\n|premium-rate telephone number\n|principal quantum number\n|private enterprise number\n|proton number\n|quantum number\n|R number\n|random number\n|registration number\n|regnal number\n|Reichert-Meissl number\n|Reichert-Meissl-Wollny number\n|research octane number\n|Reynolds number\n|Richardson number\n|ringer equivalence number\n|roll number\n|Roud number\n|round number\n|Rouse number\n|routing number\n|seed number\n|serial number\n|sex number\n|sieve number\n|silent number\n|social insurance number\n|social-security number\n|social security number\n|spin quantum number\n|Stephanus number\n|street number\n|Strouhal number\n|student number\n|subnumber\n|sunspot number\n|tailnumber\n|tail number\n|telephone number\n|tone number\n|total base number\n|unique identification number\n|unknown number\n|vanity number\n|vehicle identification number\n|version number\n|Weber number\n|weed number\n|Wolf number\n|Wratten number\n|wrong number\n|Zürich number\n}}\n{{col4|en|title=grammar: Hyponyms of \"number\"\n|abstract number\n|adverbial number\n|[[cardinal number]] ([[cardinal]])\n|[[ordinal number]] ([[ordinal]])\n|collective number\n|concrete number\n|distributive number\n|dual number\n|fractional number\n|trial number\n\n}}\n{{col4|en|title=mathematics: Hyponyms of \"number\"\n|complex number\n|even number\n|fraction\n|imaginary number\n|integer\n|integral number\n|irrational number\n|natural number\n|negative number\n|odd number\n|positive number\n|prime number\n|rational number\n|real number\n|abundant number\n|Achilles number\n|achromatic number\n|aleph number\n|algebraic number\n|autobiographical number\n|linking number\n|amicable number\n|automorphic number\n|Bell number\n|Bernoulli number\n|Betti number\n|bicomplex number\n|binary number\n|binding number\n|broken number\n|cake number\n|Carmichael number\n|Carol number\n|Catalan number\n|chromatic number\n|clique number\n|composite number\n|condition number\n|cop number\n|counting number\n|covering number\n|crossing number\n|Cullen number\n|cyclic number\n|cyclomatic number\n|decimal number\n|defective number\n|deficient number\n|Delannoy number\n|de Moivre number\n|domination number\n|double-number\n|double number\n|dual number\n|edge covering number\n|epsilon number\n|Euler's number\n|excessive number\n|Fermat number\n|Fibonacci number\n|figurate number\n|friendly number\n|Frobenius number\n|Gödel number\n|Goldbach number\n|golden number\n|Graham's number\n|Grundy number\n|hailstone number\n|happy number\n|Hardy-Ramanujan number\n|harmonic number\n|Harshad number\n|Hartogs number\n|Heegner number\n|Heesch number\n|hemiperfect number\n|hexagonal number\n|highly composite number\n|homogeneous number\n|hyperbolic number\n|hypercomplex number\n|hypernumber\n|hyperperfect number\n|hyperreal number\n|ideal number\n|independence number\n|inverse number\n|Kaprekar number\n|Keith number\n|kissing number\n|Lah number\n|Leonardo number\n|Leyland number\n|Liouville number\n|Listing number\n|Lucas number\n|Ludolphian number\n|Ludolph's number\n|Lychrel number\n|Markov number\n|matching number\n|meandric number\n|mixed number\n|Motzkin number\n|multinumber\n|multiplicative number\n|Narayana number\n|narcissistic number\n|natural number\n|neutralization number\n|neutron number\n|Newton number\n|nimber\n|Niven number\n|nonhypotenuse number\n|non-hypotenuse number\n|nonstandard number\n|nude number\n|number needed to harm\n|numeric\n|oblong number\n|p-adic number\n|pancake number\n|Pell number\n|pentatope number\n|perfect number\n|perplex number\n|Pisot number\n|Pisot-Vijayaraghavan number\n|powerful number\n|practical number\n|Proth number\n|pseudoperfect number\n|purely imaginary number\n|PV number\n|pyramidal number\n|quaternary number\n|Ramanujan-Hardy number\n|Ramsey number\n|rational number\n|rational numbers\n|Rayo's number\n|real number\n|real numbers\n|rectangular number\n|repfigit number\n|rough number\n|RSA number\n|sad number\n|Sagan's number\n|saponification number\n|Schröder number\n|semiperfect number\n|Sierpinski number\n|schizophrenic number\n|Skewes' number\n|sociable number\n|sphenic number\n|split-complex number\n|square number\n|Stirling number\n|Stirling number of the second kind\n|Stirling partition number\n|superabundant number\n|superior highly composite number\n|supernumber\n|superparticular number\n|surreal number\n|taxicab number\n|tetrahedral number\n|transcendental number\n|transfinite number\n|triangular number\n|tricomplex number\n|turning number\n|unhappy number\n|untouchable number\n|vampire number\n|vertex separation number\n|wave number\n|wavenumber\n|weird number\n|whole number\n|whole numbers\n|winding number\n|Zeisel number\n}}\n* See also [[Thesaurus:number]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en\n|abstract analytic number theory\n|age ain't nothing but a number\n|additive number theory\n|age is just a number\n|algebraic number field\n|algebraic number theory\n|algorithmic number theory\n|genuine number eleven\n|analytic number theory\n|A number 1\n|a number of\n|any number of\n|by the numbers\n|by-the-numbers\n|call someone's number\n|cloud number nine\n|color by number\n|color by numbers\n|computational number theory\n|copy number polymorphism\n|copy-number variant\n|copy number variation\n|crunch numbers\n|cushy number\n|denumber\n|do a number on\n|do numbers\n|extended real number system\n|false number 9\n|file off the serial numbers\n|fixed-point number\n|geometry of numbers|do number one|do number two\n|get someone's number\n|have one's number on it\n|have someone's number\n|int