-: Joint Hearings Before the Subcommittee on Crime of the Committee on the Judiciary and the Subcommittee on Domestic and International Scientific Planning, Analysis, and Cooperation of the Committee on Science and Technology, House of Representatives, Ninety-fifth Congress, First Session ...-->|page=107\n|text=Do they '''number''' in the hundreds, do they '''number''' in the thousands? Do they '''number''' in the tens of thousand?}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|passive}} To [[limit]] to a certain number; to [[reckon]] (as by fate) to be few in number.\n#: {{ux|en|The old man knew that his days were '''numbered'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1867|title=The Days of England Not “'''numbered'''”: Reply to Sir Archibald Alison|page=1\n|text=THE DAYS OF ENGLAND NOT “'''NUMBERED'''.” REPLY TO SIR ARCHIBALD ALISON.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2018-02-06|author=Dan Bouk|title=How Our Days Became Numbered: Risk and the Rise of the Statistical Individual|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=9780226564869|page=209\n|text=To conclude this book, we will let Lange’s photo and its three layers guide us. Each layer invites us to explore a different answer to this book's title question—how did our days become '''numbered'''?}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|literary|or|archaic}} To [[count]]; to [[determine]] the quantity of.\n#: {{ux|en|The king ordered that all his subjects be '''numbered'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Who can '''number''' all the stars and who can count the desert sands?}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1610|title=The Bible: That Is, the Holy Scriptures Contained in the Olde and New Testament, Numbers 1:3\n|text=From twentie yeare old and above, all that go forth to the warre in Iſrael, thou and Aaron ſhall '''number''' them, throughout their armies.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[label]] (items) with numbers; to [[assign]] numbers to (items).\n#: {{ux|en|'''Number''' the baskets so that we can find them easily.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1964|author=Education U.S. Department of Health (and Welfare); United States. Public Health Service|title=Public Health Service '''Numbered''' Publications: Supplement|text=“Public Health Service '''Numbered''' Publications – A Catalog, 1950-1962” and contains those '''numbered''' publications issued during the period 1963-64.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1972|author=United States. National Archives and Records Service|title=Miscellaneous Numbered Records (the Manuscript File) in the War Department Collection of Revolutionary War Records, 1775-1790's|page=3\n|text=Most of the remaining records in the War Department Collection of Revolutionary War Records were designated \"miscellaneous\" records, consecutively '''numbered''', and placed in a fourth large series of records that came to be known as {{nb...}}}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2022-09-04|author=Francis Lynde|title=The City of Numbered Days|publisher=DigiCat\n|text=The remainder of the valley is laid off into cute little squares and streets, with everything named and '''numbered''', ready to be listed in the brokers’ offices.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|with ''[[off]]''}} To [[call out]] and [[assign]] a series of numbers (usually to people), either for the sake of dividing into groups or for counting.\n#: {{ux|en|Shelley '''numbered''' off the group into two teams for the baseball game.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1870|author=USA House of Representatives|title=House Documents|page=532\n|text=I counted them and '''numbered''' them off, and I found about three hundred and seventy or three hundred and seventy-five.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2014-03-03|author=Flora Johnston|title=War Classics: The Remarkable Memoir of Scottish Scholar Christina Keith on the Western Front|publisher=The History Press|isbn=9780750956888\n|text=At my entrance, the Sergeant called them to attention, '''numbered''' them off smartly, and presented two Companies for my instruction.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|with ''[[off]]''}} To [[enumerate]] or [[list]], especially while assigning numbers to.\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2019-01-11|author=Mark G. Turner|title=We Both Shall Row, My Love And I|publisher=FriesenPress|isbn=9781525536373|page=367\n|text=I '''numbered''' them off on my fingers as I stated them. “First, I would redeem a small amount of my investment assets to pay off the cleared lot and come up with a down payment for the ten acres. Second, I would seek to obtain an open{{nb...}}}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|usually with ''[[among]]''}} To [[classify]] or [[include]] (in a group of things)\n#: {{ux|en|Alexander the Great's army '''numbered''' an elite cavalry among its ranks.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1839|author=Saint Cyprian (Bishop of Carthage.)|title=The Treatises of S. Caecilius Cyprian, Bishop of Carthage, and Martyr|page=298\n|text=We fools counted their life madness, and their end to be without honour: how are they '''numbered''' among the children of God, and their lot is among the Saints!}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1879|author=United States. Bureau of Indian Affairs|title=Report|page=76\n|text=They '''number''' among them men of intelligence and education, fitted in almost every respect to share in the responsibilities of government as well as receive a part of its benefits.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1963|author=United States. Congress. Senate. Committee on Commerce|title=Hearings|page=69\n|text=We certainly endorse the essential purpose of S. 708 — namely, that an applicant should not obtain a grant simply because it '''numbers''' among its stockholders a Member of Congress {{nb...}}}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2019-08-06|author=Fr. Joseph Irvin|title=The Divine Liturgy of St. John Chrysostom: Orthodox Service Books - Number 1|publisher=Lulu Press, Inc|isbn=9780359261604|text=Unite them to Your Holy, Catholic, and Apostolic Church, and '''number''' them with Your chosen flock. That with us they may glorify Your all-honorable and majestic name: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever and ever.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|usually with ''[[among]]''}} To be classified or included (in a certain group or category of things).\n#: {{ux|en|Her horses '''number''' among the fastest in her country.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2010-09-03|author=Catherine Tizard|title=Cat Among the Pigeons: A Memoir|publisher=Penguin Random House New Zealand Limited|isbn=9781869795863\n|text=They '''number''' among our best people, particularly when we realise that they are models for what the rest of us might also achieve.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2020-10-01|author=Elizabeth Koepping|title=Spousal Violence Among World Christians: Silent Scandal|publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing|isbn=9781350080577\n|text=If they '''number''' among those who abuse their wives, they, just like abusing leaders, should stop.}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top|to total; to amount to}}\n* Asturian: {{tt|ast|numberar}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|наброявам|impf}}, {{tt|bg|наброя|pf}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|comptar}}, {{tt+|ca|sumar}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|počítat|alt=počítat se}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|nombri}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|olla}}, {{tt+|fi|nousta}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|zählen}}\n* Gothic: {{tt|got|𐌲𐌰𐍂𐌰𐌸𐌾𐌰𐌽}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt|hu|a [[szám|száma/számuk]] (…[[van]])|lit=its/their number is…}}, {{tt+|hu|kitesz|alt=kitesz (-t)}}, {{tt+|hu|rúg|alt=rúg (-ra/-re)}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|uimhrigh}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|ammontare}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|избројува}}, {{tt|mk|набројува}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|liczyć|impf}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|amontar}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|насчи́тывать}}, {{tt+|ru|исчисля́ться}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|saymak}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to be limited to a certain number}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|преброен съм|impf}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-also|literary: to count|count}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|преброявам|impf}}, {{t|bg|преброя|pf}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|nombrer}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|label with numbers; assign numbers to}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|رَقَّمَ}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Syriac: {{tt|syc|ܡܢܐ|tr=mna}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|համարակալել}}\n* Asturian: {{tt|ast|numberar}}\n* Breton: {{tt|br|niverenniñ}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|номерирам}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|numerar}}\n* Czech: {{tt|cs|číslovat}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|nummeren}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|numeri}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|numeroida}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|numéroter}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|nummerieren}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|αριθμώ}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מספר|m|tr=misper}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|megszámoz}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt|is|númera}}, {{tt|is|tölusetja}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt|ia|numerar}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|uimhrigh}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|numerare}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|numerare}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|numurēt}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|нумери́ра}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|numerować}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|numerar}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|numerota}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|нумерова́ть}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{tt|dsb|cysłowaś|impf}}, {{tt|dsb|numerěrowaś|impf}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|numerar}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|numrera}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|numaralamak}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|rhifo}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to call out and assign numbers}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|преброявам|impf}}, {{t|bg|преброя|pf}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-also|to enumerate|enumerate}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|изброявам|impf}}, {{t|bg|изброя|pf}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|dénombrer}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to classify or include (among)}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|включвам|impf}}, {{t|bg|включа|pf}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|compter}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to be classified or included (among)}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|съм сред}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|compter}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n}}\n\n=====See also=====\n* {{sense|grammatical numbers}} {{l|en|singular}}, [[dual]], [[trial]], [[quadral]], [[paucal]], [[plural]], [[singulative]]\n* [[Appendix:Numbers|Wiktionary’s Appendix of numbers]]\n\n=====References=====\n* {{pedia}}\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|en|more numb}} From {{m|en|numb|pos=adjective}} + {{m|en|-er}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{enPR|nŭm'ə|a=RP}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈnʌmə/}}\n* {{enPR|nŭm'ər|a=US}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈnʌmɚ/}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-number-adjective.ogg|a=US|pos=adjective}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|numb|er}}\n\n====Adjective====\n{{head|en|comparative adjective}}\n\n# {{en-comparative of|numb}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\nEquivalent to {{af|en|numb|-er|pos1=verb|id2=agent noun}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{enPR|nŭm'ə|a=RP}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈnʌmə/}}\n* {{enPR|nŭm'ər|a=US}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈnʌmɚ/}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|numb|er}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# Something that [[numbs]].\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=bemnru|numbre|renumb}}\n\n{{cln|en|heteronyms}}\n{{C|en|Arithmetic|Parts of speech}}\n\n==Estonian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|et|nr||abbreviation}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|et|de|Nummer}}. The added -b- is analogous to {{m|et|kamber}} and {{m|et|klamber}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{et-IPA}}\n* {{rhymes|et|umber|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|et|num|ber}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{et-noun|numbri|numbrit}}\n\n# [[#English|number]] {{gl|the symbol representing the number, its character}}\n# [[number plate]], [[licence plate]], [[license plate]]\n#: {{syn|et|numbrimärk}}\n# [[#English|number]] {{gl|periodical (numbered) single issue}}\n#: {{syn|et|ajalehenumber}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{et-decl-õpik|numb|ri|er}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Sõnaveeb}}\n* {{R:et:EKSS}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|nombre}}\n\n==Papiamentu==\n[[File:Waehlscheibe-kurzwahlnummern.jpg|200px|right]]\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|pap|en|number}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|pap|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|number}}"}}